==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Alizarine
<hw>A*liz"a*rine</hw></mhw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>alizarine</ets>, fr.
<ets>alizari</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A coloring principle,
<chform>C14H6O2(OH)2</chform>, found in madder, and now produced
artificially as an an orange-red crystalline compound from anthracene.
It is used in making red pigments (such as the Turkish reds), and in
dyeing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alkahest</ent>⟦br⟧
